    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team determined that the aggregate evidence across 13 factors, combined with Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification and three-laboratory experimental comparison, is sufficient to support regulatory submission. Minor shortfalls in model form uncertainty (18% vs 15% criterion) and test condition equivalency are judged acceptable given the conservative clinical threshold margin demonstrated by the 95th-percentile NIH value. The central claim that NIH remains below the absolute clinical threshold is considered substantiated by the body of work documented in this package.",
